		<note type="note">Port 11213 is an internal port used on the local host for memcached 
			and triggering manual compaction. The port is not used for communication between cluster nodes. 
			For firewall purposes, you do not need to take port 11213 into consideration. 
			However, if another service is listening on this port, 
			the Couchbase Server service will not start. </note>
		
